        </p>
        <p>
            4.  Calculate the reciprocal of <m>10^3</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
            Since <m>10^3</m> can be written as <m>1000</m> then its reciprocal is <m>\frac{1}{1000}</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
            5. Multiply <m>0.787</m> by <m>\frac{1}{1000}</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
            6. Hence, the reciprocal of <m>1252</m> is given by <m>0.787 \times \frac{1}{1000} = 0.000787</m> 
        </p>
