        <p>
           4. Maria conducted  a survey to determine how many students love to play games, <m>0.256</m> of respondents preferred playing football. 
              To represent this as a fraction in the form <m>1/n</m>, what is the value of <m>n</m>? Use mathematical tables to determine your answer.
        </p>
        <p>
           5. A farmer can plant <m>7.85</m> acres of land in one day. 
              The time taken to plant one acre is the reciprocal of this rate. Using mathematical tables, find how many days it takes to plant one acre of land.
        </p>
        <p>
           6. John can type 80 words per minute. He wondered how long it takes him to write one word.
              Find out how long it takes John to type one word . Hence determine how long it will take John to type a 400-word essay.
