    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-finding-reciprocals-using-a-calculator">
        <title>Finding reciprocals using a calculator</title>
       
        
                <p>
                To find reciprocal of a number using a calculator:  
                </p>
               <image source="/cal.jpeg">
                <shortdescription></shortdescription>
               </image>
                <p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Enter the number into the calculator,
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Press the reciprocal button <m>{\color{red} x^{-1}}</m> or divide <m>1</m> by the number.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Read the displayed result.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Example: To find the reciprocal of <m>7</m>,
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="i)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                            Press the key <m>1</m>  
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Press the key <m>\div</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Press the key <m>7</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Press the key <m>=</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Read the displayed result which is <m>0.14285714286</m>. Hence the reciprocal of <m>7</m> is <m>0.1429</m>
                </p>
